Here's someone right now who's fixing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending right now that I still have a job and am working from home while I'm sitting on Too Hot to Handle.
If I could damn it all, manage to open the file. (F*** OneDrive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Hurrah.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to turn my air purifier all the way up, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would actually be completely okay even if he weren't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
At least I have finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn scary. Oh yeah, that's the good stuff!
I do Search and Replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I stand by that. Natural language is usually fragmented, especially when one becomes emotional.
The craftsman is now at work with the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (at least that's how it sounds). I secretly checked how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(.
Still 7 pages left in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite well done – mostly changes to the text and very minor corrections in direct speech, and I still need to phrase everything a bit more concisely. But I could really use a break and a cup of tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he has just started vacuuming dust again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen type is gone!
He told me he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too cheap and only paid for the part next to the door that wasn't in good condition. Feels a lot better now.
The house is being ventilated, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I drink tea in the garden!
